d moderate CYP450 2D6 inhibitors include abiraterone, bupropion, celecoxib, cimetidine, cinacalcet, clobazam, darifenacin, diphenhydramine, duloxetine, fluoxetine, methotrimeprazine, mirabegron, paroxetine, propoxyphene, quinidine, ranolazine, sertraline, stiripentol, and terbinafine.', 'Metabolism', NULL, NULL, 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/97298/', '[1] "Product Information. Cerdelga (eliglustat)." Genzyme Corporation, Cambridge, MA.[2] "Product Information. Cerdelga (eliglustat)." Genzyme Corporation, Cambridge, MA.', 1767365206);
